find a: set  of int(1..4)
find b: set  of int(1..4)

such that

(sum(flatten([[ sum([i,j;int(1..2)]) | j : int(1..3), i <- a ],[ sum([i,j;int(1..2)]) | j : int(1..3), i <- b, !(i in a) ];int(1..)])) = 10)

Model before rewriting:

find a: set  of int(1..4)
find b: set  of int(1..4)

such that

(sum([ sum([i,j;int(1..2)]) | j : int(1..3), i <- (a union b) ]) = 10)

--

[ sum([i,j;int(1..2)]) | j : int(1..3), i <- (a union b) ], 
   ~~> union_set ([("Base", 8700)])
flatten([[ sum([i,j;int(1..2)]) | j : int(1..3), i <- a ],[ sum([i,j;int(1..2)]) | j : int(1..3), i <- b, !(i in a) ];int(1..)])

--

Final model:

find a: set  of int(1..4)
find b: set  of int(1..4)

such that

(sum(flatten([[ sum([i,j;int(1..2)]) | j : int(1..3), i <- a ],[ sum([i,j;int(1..2)]) | j : int(1..3), i <- b, !(i in a) ];int(1..)])) = 10)

